12 nursing program for at least five (5) years may increase the
13 enrollment in any eligible nursing program at any rate the
14 institution considers appropriate.
15 (d) A nursing program that:
16 (1) is operated by a postsecondary educational institution, as
17 defined in IC 21-7-13-6(a)(1);
18 (2) was accredited by the board on a date after June 30, 2020; and
19 (3) has been operating for at least one (1) year;
20 may increase its enrollment rate by not more than one hundred percent
21 (100%).
